which is a TaÃ­no term

00:01:52.900 --> 00:01:56.466
for a type of rodent

00:01:56.466 --> 00:01:58.800
that has almost become extinct

00:01:59.600 --> 00:02:00.600
and nowadays

00:02:00.600 --> 00:02:04.566
you can only find them in some isolated parts

00:02:04.566 --> 00:02:05.466
of Hispaniola

00:02:06.033 --> 00:02:09.366
it is absent in Puerto Rico or the Virgin Islands

00:02:09.400 --> 00:02:13.100
and Cuba still has a population

00:02:13.100 --> 00:02:14.500
we don't know how large

00:02:15.100 --> 00:02:17.700
it was obviously overhunted

00:02:18.766 --> 00:02:20.600
probably

00:02:20.900 --> 00:02:23.766
the population increased when the Spaniards began to arrive

00:02:23.766 --> 00:02:26.900
and immigration started

